- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with combinatorial problems related to binary words and abelian borders. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with binary words and their properties. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the exact number of binary words of a given length with certain properties. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of counting the number of binary words with certain properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses results from lattice paths and generalizes them to partial words.
